A police officer of Malvern SAPS tested positive for the coronavirus (Covid-19), on Thursday, 25 June. The affected building is being decontaminated as per SAPS protocols and all other officials that were exposed to the police officer were directed to undergo screening and testing as a precaution. Provincial police spokesperson, Brigadier Jay Naicker said: “The community service centre is currently operating at an alternative building within the police station premises while the decontamination takes place.” Service delivery will not be hampered during this process. Citizens can contact the police station on 031 489-9629/33/35 or the Station Commander, Colonel Reddy on 082-418-0743.